From: Kush Gupta <kugupta@redhat.com>
Date: Wed, 11 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] cmake: fix install LIBDIR on Fedora Rawhide (CMake 4.0+)

In CMake 3.x GNUInstallDirs sets CMAKE_INSTALL_LIBDIR as both a cache
variable and a normal variable.  The flux-sched CMakeLists.txt overrides
the cache with FORCE to match flux-core's libdir, but this does not
update the normal variable that shadows it.  On CMake 4.0+ (Fedora
Rawhide), install() uses the normal variable, causing libraries to be
installed to the build directory instead of the intended prefix.

Fix by also setting the normal (non-cache) variable so both agree.

---
 CMakeLists.txt | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -84,6 +84,7 @@ else()
   set(FLUX_CORE_LIBEXT "${CMAKE_INSTALL_LIBDIR}")
 endif()
 set(CMAKE_INSTALL_LIBDIR ${FLUX_CORE_LIBEXT} CACHE PATH "..." FORCE)
+set(CMAKE_INSTALL_LIBDIR ${FLUX_CORE_LIBEXT})
 message(STATUS "Forcing libdir selection to match flux-core: prefix subdir (${FLUX_CORE_LIBEXT})")
 message(STATUS "    flux-core library path: (${FLUX_CORE_LIBDIR})")
 message(STATUS "    flux-sched library path: (${CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX}/${FLUX_CORE_LIBEXT})")
